+# Wine Stock Report Generator
+
+**Wine Stock Report Generator** converts a real warehouse stock-on-hand CSV into a readable Markdown stock report, including finished wine stock, 9LE totals, grouping summaries, low-stock warnings, dry goods, and data validation notes.
+
+---
+
+## What it does
+
+- Loads a warehouse stock CSV file exported from a warehouse management system.
+- Separates Finished Goods (wine) from Dry Goods (labels, packaging, etc.).
+- Parses wine metadata from product descriptions (vintage, variety, market, bottle size, pack size).
+- Calculates 9-litre-equivalent (9LE) stock using `Decimal` arithmetic.
+- Groups the summary by variety, vintage, market, pack size, lot, or none.
+- Identifies low-stock items below a configurable 9LE threshold.
+- Generates a structured Markdown report.
+- Runs interactively (asks six clarification questions) or non-interactively.
+
+---
+
+## Requirements
+
+- Python 3.11 or later
+- Standard library only — no external packages required
+
+---
+
+## How to run
+
+### Interactive mode (default)
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv
+```
+
+The program loads the CSV, prints a detection summary, and asks six questions:
+
+```text
+1. Use OnHand or Available stock for wine totals? [Available]
+2. Include Dry Goods section? [yes]
+3. Group primary wine summary by variety, vintage, market, pack_size, lot, or none? [variety]
+4. Include low-stock warnings? [yes]
+5. Low-stock threshold in 9LE? [10]
+6. Output filename? [stock-report.md]
+```
+
+Press Enter to accept each default. On EOF (e.g. piped empty input), all defaults are accepted:
+
+```bash
+printf '' | python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv
+```
+
+### Non-interactive mode
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv \
+  --basis Available \
+  --group-by variety \
+  --include-dry-goods \
+  --low-stock-warnings \
+  --low-stock-threshold 10 \
+  --output stock-report.md \
+  --no-interactive
+```
+
+---
+
+## Command-line flags
+
+| Flag | Values | Default | Description |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `CSV_PATH` | path | (required) | Path to the warehouse stock CSV file |
+| `--basis` | `OnHand`, `Available` | `Available` | Stock quantity basis for wine totals |
+| `--group-by` | `variety`, `vintage`, `market`, `pack_size`, `lot`, `none` | `variety` | Group primary wine summary by this field |
+| `--include-dry-goods` | (flag) | on | Include a Dry Goods section in the report |
+| `--no-dry-goods` | (flag) | — | Exclude the Dry Goods section |
+| `--low-stock-warnings` | (flag) | on | Include low-stock warnings in the report |
+| `--no-low-stock-warnings` | (flag) | — | Exclude low-stock warnings |
+| `--low-stock-threshold N` | decimal | `10` | Low-stock threshold in 9LE |
+| `--output PATH` | path | `stock-report.md` | Output file path |
+| `--no-interactive` | (flag) | off | Skip all prompts; use effective CLI option values |
+
+---
+
+## Exit codes
+
+| Code | Meaning |
+|---:|---|
+| 0 | Success |
+| 1 | Data or file error (missing file, missing required column, unreadable CSV) — message on stderr |
+| 2 | Usage error (unknown flag, bad argument value) — argparse-native |
+
+---
+
+## Example commands
+
+```bash
+# Basic interactive run
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv
+
+# Non-interactive with all options
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv \
+  --no-interactive \
+  --basis OnHand \
+  --group-by vintage \
+  --no-dry-goods \
+  --low-stock-threshold 5 \
+  --output onhand-report.md
+
+# Group by market
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv \
+  --no-interactive --group-by market --output market-report.md
+
+# No grouping, no low-stock section
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv \
+  --no-interactive --group-by none --no-low-stock-warnings
+```
+
+---
+
+## Running tests
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests
+```
+
+---
+
+## Project structure
+
+```text
+wine_stock_reporter/
+  __init__.py       — package metadata
+  __main__.py       — entry point (python3 -m wine_stock_reporter)
+  cli.py            — argument parsing, interactive prompts, main() orchestration
+  csv_loader.py     — CSV loading, column validation, numeric cleaning
+  models.py         — dataclasses: StockRow, ParsedWineRow, ReportOptions, ValidationWarning
+  parser.py         — description parser, variety mapping, vintage expansion
+  calculations.py   — 9LE calculation, aggregation, low-stock identification
+  validation.py     — row-level data quality checks
+  report.py         — Markdown report renderer
+tests/
+  test_csv_loader.py
+  test_parser.py
+  test_calculations.py
+  test_validation.py
+  test_report.py
+examples/
+  stock_sample.csv  — fixture CSV
+```
+
+---
+
+## Input CSV format
+
+The required columns are:
+
+```text
+Type1, Item, Description, OnHand, Warehouse, Allocated, Pending, Available, Units
+```
+
+Optional columns (may be empty):
+
+```text
+ClientStockCode, ClientStockDescription, Lot
+```
+
+Known `Type1` values: `Finished Goods`, `Dry Goods`.
+Known `Units` values: `Cases` (wine), `Eaches` (dry goods).
+
+---
+
+## 9LE calculation
+
+9-litre-equivalents = `quantity × pack_size × bottle_size_litres / 9`
+
+| Bottle size | Pack | 9LE per case |
+|---|---:|---:|
+| 750 ml | 12 | 1.00 |
+| 750 ml | 6 | 0.50 |
+| 375 ml | 12 | 0.50 |
+
+All calculations use Python `decimal.Decimal`; report values are rounded to two decimal places.
